reenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> At this point in my Mage's career, I have to decide between these two soloing strategies. If I am fighting a high blue or white (or maybe even yellow) enemy, should I nuke the hell out of the enemy, or concentrate on healing my pet? My best DD spells at this point are Shock of Blades or Collumn of Fire. I figure three or four of these spells will take off more that half of the enemy's health, but would leave me with alot less that half mana. In the meantime, my pet is taking a beating, and even then the mob could aggro on me. <br>
Another tactic: Concentrate on healing and buffing my pet. At this point, I can use Fire Sheild and Burnout to buff my pet. I also have renew elements, but I have noticed that this is usually innefective, and I don't usually notice alot of added health to my pet. What do you think?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/01 5:39:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> shock of blade? so you're between level 8 and 15. I never try renew element. Wait for level 20 pet heal, much better. Best strategy I found is to send pet in and nuke to the hell. If your level 8 to 11, stay at east common hunt young kodiak and snakes. That giant snake fangs sell good. My new magician (this time a DE, and just got level 12 tonight) just spent one evening tonight at West common land hunting wisp. He made 2 and a half bubble exp, and about 50 pp. I bought all level 16 spells that I will need. and that's it. I can go wherever I want and hunt whatever I want. No need to worry about money any more, well, don't have to worry about it before level 16 anyway. Young Kodiak, ASP, Wisp, and that big green snake whatever the name is, never aggro me no matter how much I nuke.<br>
By the way, after level 16, my human mage was hunting NK for griffawn, those things aggros if you nuke too much.<br>
 <p>Mejision - level 23 Human Mage<BR>
Yishen - level 10 Human Cleric<BR>
Woofwoof - level 14 Bard shaman<BR>
Zlazher - level 16 Troll SK<BR>
Monnkey - level 16 Human Monk<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/01 5:26:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> by the way, don't use shock of blades, use the bolt. It does more damages. But if you're hunting in Lavastorm, bolt will be resisted 100%, use shock of blades and ward summon.<br>
<br>
 <p>level 23 Human Mage<BR>
level 12 DE Mage<BR>
level 10 Human Cleric<BR>
level 14 Barb shaman<BR>
level 16 Troll SK<BR>
