</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uakeintp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akein TP</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/01 7:24:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://stratege.gameland.ru/forum/pic/35.jpg HIGHT = 161 WIDTH = 65></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> Nuking was always better exp for me if i was soloing since then you outdamage pet and it doesnt eat 50% of your exp.<br>
Also mob dies faster so you waste less time fighting.<br>
 <p>Akein the Conjurer <br>
Rebirth of Tholuxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukjeldon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeldon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/01 1:19:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ...</span><hr size=1> Right now Im soloing Wooly Mammoths in Everfrost, what I do is Nuke, 2 Heals, Nuke, Pet Recast, Nuke. Assuming no resists the Mammoth is dead!<br>
<br>
Phamyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waldenawildfyre>Waldena Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/01 4:36:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I dont really see the point in healing your pet if your gonna recast it later in the fight.  Seems kinda like a waste of mana.  Id either heal the pet enough so it lives the whole fight, or use no heals and just remake pet when it gets low. <p><b>Waldena Wildfyre <Knights of the Tribunal>
