<i>"Summon someone who gives a damn"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/01 5:19:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> the only time I use pet heal is after a fight, and I found myself full mana, but pet is not full health yet. So I cast heal to kinda balance my mana and pet's health a bit. By the time I get full mana again, pet will be full health as well.<br>
 <p>level 23 Human Mage<BR>
