level 6 barb rogue<BR>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uscrubfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scrubfire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/01 12:40:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> When you get to 39, you probably will never heal your pet again after battle.  Their regen rate is insane, and they will often regen fully before you have meditated for a bubble of mana.<br>
<br>
That being said, I still use pet heal once in a while, especially when I have the highest hitting pet.  What a pain to get a good pet, Buff it, and lose it.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>--------------------------
Kennethjames Scrubfire
Mage of the 40th Summoning, Mithaniel Marr
Member of the guild Vanguard of Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udeltanamossumnorxegony.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deltanamos Sumnor Xegony</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(4/14/01 8:15:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> Depends on the level of the mob, the pet heal spells stop at 24 with renew elements so savor it while you can. If the mob is blue dont pay too much attention to healing pet, instead concentrate on nuking but watch his health using /pet report health periodically just to see. If the mob is yellow (or even red ive found at teens) worry about keeping him healed, heal nuke nuke heal nuke nuke repeat. Your pet is your lifeline and since you havent gotten speialize the chances of you getting gate off with a mob on you are slim. Be careful out there, the blasting strategy is only useful against weaker/even mobs or in groups. A good idea when soloing the bigguns is to DS and burnout your pet constantly, make sure those are always on while fighting. It also doesnt hurt to equip your pet with a weapon, best in my opinion for pets is a gnoll hide lariat (stun effect). GL =)<br>
<br>
Deltanamos Sumnor<br>
51st Magician on Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=balthemal>Balthemal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(5/30/01 7:53:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> Healing pets is a great thing in some situations and levels. For example, right now, as I'm hunting Gorlas in TD, I would not survive wihtout pet heal. Yes, I could use an earthpet, get the mob rooted, and nuke to hell. However, I've found that using the pet heal can mean that you use less mana during a fight than if you nuked. The key is this: Do you heal, so the pet can live longer? Or do you nuke, so the mob will die faster.<br>
Well, if you nuke it to death, the mob will die and your pet will live. So that solves that, right? Not quite <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Another factor is aggro. If you're back there blasting away, most mobs will not like it very much and start beating you. This is very bad for mages, as we have NO means of crowd control save our pets. No root, no fear, no mez, and no stun. Just good old Zoner <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
Usuing the earth pet can negate the aggro factor, but the earth root is not the most reliable (personal opinion...errr so is everything else in this, I guess, lol). So, I would say that a combination of heal and nuking is best, although the previous poster was correct in that you will want to stop this at 39, when pet regen goes into high gear, so to speak.<br>
It does depend on the pet, by the way. For the earth pet, you can nuke more (Has more hps and roots to negate aggro). With the fire pet, you will want to heal more (less hp and the damage shield makes up for lack of nukes)<br>
Well, that's all I can think of. Feel free to ridiclue my ideas, just don't say anything about my spelling. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>Balthemal says: "Save me, Jboots, save me!"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=balthemal>Balthemal</A> at: 5/31/01 5:48:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucbruzer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CBruzer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/01 7:16:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Soloing</span><hr size=1> I am Level 23 and I love the air pet. I can nuke a mob to pull it to me, at the EXTREME range of my flame bolt spell. I'll have enough time to cast a 2nd flame bolt, then send pet to attack, while running in reverse. After nailing a mob for 152 twice, they are pretty much hell bent on killing you, but the air pets stun stops it long enough for you to keep your distance, and nuke again as neccessary. If the Mob does catch up to you, just keep walking back until you can find help, or your pet stuns it again. Really effective with SoW because you can keep a safe distance against most everything. This works great against blues, your pet will continually nail the mob from behind, and stun it. I imagine this would work with the earth pet, but i've yet to test this. I will as soon as I hit 24.<br>
<br>
Kelebek Channelar<br>
23rd Level Mage<br>
Mithaniel Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=balthemal>Balthemal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/01 11:46:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> Not to sound rude....but what does this have to do with the topic at hand? <p>Balthemal says: "Save me, Jboots, save me!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulionfrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lionfrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 1:21:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing strategy: Nuke or heal?</span><hr size=1> Personally, at lvl 20 I never had my heal spell memmed, I bought it yes, I just never used it. I don't see a huge difference in hp. <br>
<br>
When I was lvl 20 I could blast the mob for 152<br>
<br>
